 (20+ members, avg lvl 30), so I don't have access to high level raids or large sums of cash other than what I can loot myself in the coming levels.  Any zone suggestions for 34-40 would also be appreciated (loot/exp).  Thanks for your time and input, seems that this message board is one of the best references for EQ paladins available.<br><br>P.S. Don't rip my name apart ), I know it's unfitting of a paladin.<br><br>Pirator<br>Paladin of the 34th Season (Mithaniel Marr)<br>Zebuxoruk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udelsinionbarlepop.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Delsinion Barlepop</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/28/02 11:57:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=330.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.lazykatcreations.com/images/Sdallas_small.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Equipment check for a level 34 nontwink</span><hr size=1> Start looking into some ac/hp rings, change one bracer to crustacean and start saving for haste then deepwater.  Since this is your first you are very well equiped, at least much better than I was at your level.  Your 2hs will hold you into the mid 40's I imagine or get an arbitor's combine greatsword if you can find one on the cheap.<br><br>&lt;edit&gt;  Also, your #1 priority should be the haste, then one more stamina item... the 1hs/2hs will fall in line after those, but they are not huge upgrades for you right now, buy stuff that will do you the most good, not just marginal gains. <p>"Let's get into trouble, baby"<BR><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=83637">Delsinion Barlepop: the pally</a><BR><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=83695">Elewood Ballues: the beastlord</a><BR><BR><a target="new"href=http://bladesandmagic.guildworld.com>Blades and Magic</a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udelsinionbarlepop.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Delsinion Barlepop</A> at: 3/28/02 12:01:01 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueggolas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eggolas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/28/02 1:35:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=330.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Equipment check for a level 34 nontwink</span><hr size=1> Ghoulbane quest is always nice, but the ION spell works exceedingly well with a fast 1-hander or 2-hander.  A Centi Warspear (200pp) at 20/30 might fill the gap, or a Centi SS (12/25 200pp), Smoldering Brand (9/22 1HB 50-100pp) or Goranga Spiked Club (12/23 IHB).  The BABS is just fine.  I'm still using mine at level 43.<br><br>In fact, you have much the same equipment at 34 that I have at 43.<br><br>The third item on your list, haste, is almost a religion around here.  Thus, I'll offer a heretical approach.  I don't have haste and never have had such an item.  Faster weapons can make a world of difference as will keeping your AC at highest levels possible for the mobs being fought.  It also helps to make friends with a Shaman.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Seriously, haste is expensive on items and the camps are generally overrun with farmers, making for a frustrating experience.  You'll do fine, perhaps even better, focusing on better weaponry at cheap prices and better AC/HP on items.<br><br>It will cost far less also.<br><br>Finally, I view this game, for a non-twink, as one of incremental betterment.  As you progress through leveling, you fight different mobs in solo and group settings.  You can afford to keep upgrading in increments until you reach 49, at which time self-haste and a fast weapon will do wonders.  Focus on AC first and HP second.  It's cheap, it's readity available and you'll notice immediate improvements in how far down your health bubble goes.<br><br>Eggolas Moria<br>Paladin of Prexus - 43rd<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugrimand.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimand</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/28/02 2:21:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=330.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Equipment check for a level 34 nontwink</span><hr size=1> Just use the best stuff you can find.  Don't bother buying equipment, it's not worth it.  People that buy equipment generally can't be trusted to have a clue how to play thier character. <p><center><img src="http://www.twilightavengers.org/sigs/grimand.jpg"></center><center>Level 53 Cavalier</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uangelsyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Angelsyn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 248<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/28/02 3:03:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=330.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Equipment check for a level 34 nontwink</span><hr size=1> 1) Sporali Defender's Blade &gt; Ghoulbane.  You'll still want the Ghoulbane for your Epic eventually though.<br><br>2) Centi Warspear &amp; Centi Shortsword are excellent, and cheap.<br><br>3) Get started on your Ro!  Ro Helm, Ro Greaves &amp; Ro Boots.<br><br>4) Take a friend or two and camp for the Hero Bracer.  Make absolutely sure your faction is high enough. (I blew it once, myself and had to go back.)<br><br>5) Eventually, you'll want a DW Helm... but don't rush for it.<br><br>6) Take a tracker &amp; hunt up the Heretics in Stonebrunt for a Swiftclaw Sash.  Might want to go as a trio at your level.<br><br>7) Don't try too bloody hard to get the Ro Vambraces &amp; Ro Bracers.  DW Goblins in RM are tough, and the Plague Shark in Erud's x-ing is nasty, rare, and stubborn about dropping the portions. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulargar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Largar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/29/02 5:50:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=330.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://giant-robot.freeyellow.com/images/giant_robot_head.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Equipment check for a level 34 nontwink</span><hr size=1> Untill you get a piece of haste armor, you best bet for 2hs is a mithril 2 handed sword it just plain out rocks! A close second is a centi spear, but its piercing, so one of each would be nice. The good thing is they are both dirt cheap.<br><br>A good place to hunt? Thurgadian mines if you have velious. Every so often you can go into the next zone and see if people killing dwarfs will let you loot some royal frosted velium armor. It's no drop and most people there will have better (unless they're outfitting a twink). The boots drop alot, and would be a big upgrade for ya.<br><br>For an ac 9 bracer with some stats, you can go kill the bandit lord in warsliks woods. You should be able to solo him, and it takes about an hour or two.<br><br>For a nice range item, look into curfang's heart, which drops in halowshade moor. You can probably solo this too, a partner wouldnt hurt though. Again, takes about an hour.<br><br>Good luck to ya <p><span style='filter:glow(color=#00FFFF,strength=2);width:100%'>C r u s</span></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showPrevMessage?topicID=330.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showNextMessage?topicID=330.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=330.topic&index=5><img src=http://eq1.castersrealm.com/pon/images/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.emailToFriend?topicID=330.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.threadControl?topicID=330.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=330.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http